MitelIfType.name: MitelIfType
MitelIfType.description: The MITEL-defined interface type. Additions to this list must be provided by the MITEL Standards Group.

MitelNotifyTransportType.name: MitelNotifyTransportType
MitelNotifyTransportType.description: The method of transporting a notification to an interested manager.

mitelIdentification.name: mitelIdentification
mitelIdentification.description: The identification subtree. Leaves in this subtree are used for the sysObjectID field in the MIB-II system tree or other similar OID fields.

mitelExperimental.name: mitelExperimental
mitelExperimental.description: The experimental MIB development subtree. The branches in this subtree should follow the format of the mitelProprietary subtree.

mitelExtensions.name: mitelExtensions
mitelExtensions.description: The standards extension subtree. Used for extensions to any of the standard subtrees under the MIB-II subtree.

mitelProprietary.name: mitelProprietary
mitelProprietary.description: The managed information subtree. Leaves in this subtree are generic devices or protocols that can be managed.

mitelConformance.name: mitelConformance
mitelConformance.description: The conformance subtree. Leaves in this subtree identify compliance grouping and requirements.

mitelIdMgmtPlatforms.name: mitelIdMgmtPlatforms
mitelIdMgmtPlatforms.description: Products used to manage MITEL equipment.

mitelIdInterfaces.name: mitelIdInterfaces
mitelIdInterfaces.description: Products providing the interface between a call processing entity and a network or terminal.

mitelIdApplicationPlatforms.name: mitelIdApplicationPlatforms
mitelIdApplicationPlatforms.description: Products providing application-based platforms that provide value-added capabilities.

mitelIdCs2000Light.name: mitelIdCs2000Light
mitelIdCs2000Light.description: The Mitel SX-2000 LIGHT Call Server.

mitelIdCsIpera3000.name: mitelIdCsIpera3000
mitelIdCsIpera3000.description: The MITEL Networks 3300 ICP Call Server.

mitelExtInterfaces.name: mitelExtInterfaces
mitelExtInterfaces.description: Proprietary extensions to the MIB-II subtree.

mitelIfNumber.name: mitelIfNumber
mitelIfNumber.description: The number of MITEL proprietary interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

mitelIfTable.name: mitelIfTable
mitelIfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of mitelIfNumber. The table consists of one row for each MITEL-specific interface, and is indexed by the ifIndex value of the corresponding row in the MIB-II ifTable.

mitelIfTableEntry.name: mitelIfTableEntry
mitelIfTableEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

mitelIfTblType.name: mitelIfTblType
mitelIfTblType.description: The type of interface. Additional values for mitelIfTblType are assigned by the Standards Group, through updating the syntax of the MitelIfType textual convention. This row is deleted automatically when the corresponding ifTable row is deleted.

mitelPropNotifications.name: mitelPropNotifications
mitelPropNotifications.description: Control and history of proprietary notifications.

mitelPropReset.name: mitelPropReset
mitelPropReset.description: Access for remote reset of agent and platform.

mitelPropCommon.name: mitelPropCommon
mitelPropCommon.description: Manageable of common information that can span hardware, middleware, and utilities.

mitelConfCompliances.name: mitelConfCompliances
mitelConfCompliances.description: The compliance subtree. Leaves in this subtree are used for defining the ways in which an agent can claim compliance with this or other MITEL MIBs.

mitelConfGroups.name: mitelConfGroups
mitelConfGroups.description: The group subtree. Leaves in this subtree identify object groupings used in the compliance statements.

mitelGrpCommon.name: mitelGrpCommon
mitelGrpCommon.description: The groups associated with the MITEL MIB.

mitelGrpCs2000.name: mitelGrpCs2000
mitelGrpCs2000.description: The groups associated with the MITEL SX2000 MIB.

mitelGrpIpera3000.name: mitelGrpIpera3000
mitelGrpIpera3000.description: The groups associated with the MITEL 3300 ICP MIB.

mitelConfAgents.name: mitelConfAgents
mitelConfAgents.description: The agent capabilities subtree. Leaves in this subtree are used for defining the capabilities of a particular agent implementation regarding the MIB compliance statements.

mitelComplMitel.name: mitelComplMitel
mitelComplMitel.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the MITEL MIB.

mitelGrpCmnInterfaces.name: mitelGrpCmnInterfaces
mitelGrpCmnInterfaces.description: The objects in the MIB-II interfaces extension.
